Busisiwe Mkhwebane says her office is working with the Auditor-General to probe the R10-million project. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Public Protector is investigating the controversial Eastern Cape scooter ambulance purchase. Busisiwe Mkhwebane says her office is working with the Auditor-General on the R10-million project.  READ: Public Protector to probe COVID-19 complaints Health Minister Zweli Mkhize said last month the scooter ambulances don't meet the basic criteria for transporting patients. The Eastern Cape health department defended its decision to spend millions on the scooter project. READ: Mkhize: Eastern Cape scooter ambulances fail to meet standards Mkhwebane said her office "has over the last four months seen a rapid surge in the number of complaints of conduct and service failure relating to the pandemic". "We have been consistent in our call on the bureaucracy to exercise prudence when it comes to spending public funds on COVID-19 related goods and services," Mkhwebane said in a statement. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. -- Additional reporting AFP